	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Are you sure ? I once disassembled my Starfox card and I was pretty sure only one pin was grounded or something like that. Same for Yoshi's Island.</div>
<br />
<br />Starfox does use pin1, it's connected to L1 (ferrite bead), then to 3 pin on a small ic (might be an inverter or buffer) then to pin 70 on the sfx (CLK), pin 70 is also connected to a resistor (1kOhm) to ground 
<br />
<br />so yes it's used on that one

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


